CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 3, 1956, pg. 10, reads: "Criminal Court Judge Sends Yorkrite Masons' Records to Philly U. S. Court - Fraudulent Conversion Charges Postponed 'Til Federal Court Rules - York Masons' Fight - As George W. Dudley (behind unidentified man on right facing the camera) confers with a Courier reporter, four other York Rite Masons gathered around while awaiting the assignment of a case against Dudley and six others to a Criminal Courier to answer charges preferred by A. W. Welch. Welch claims that he, not Dudley, is the Most Worshipful Grand Master of the Pennsylvania Lodge. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, including George W. Dudley, and other members of York Rite Masons standing in Allegheny County Courthouse corridor with overhead sign reading "Witness Room, witnesses must report here and remain until called"
